# üêû bug report

### Affected Package
The issue is caused by an incorrect behavior of formatDate function available inside @angular/common package. This is specific to Korean culture.

### Description
We've written a custom pipe to represent time based on the selected language & format. One of the scenario where function is not behaving properly is as follow;

- If a combination of Korean language( ko, ko-KR cultures) and 12 hour format('mediumTime' or 'hh:mm:ss a') is selected then it is not showing AM/PM in Korean culture. It simply prints output as **'PM 6:02:16'** , whereas, the expected output is **'Ïò§ÌõÑ 6:02:16'** 

If you set the locale as German then it properly converts the AM/PM.

I've verified that findLocaleData() for 'kr' culture has relevant data available, however, it is returning AM-PM instead of culture related values.

